</title>
<subSubSection id="3FF170BC077C3C98BD11338F2A2C97AD" pageId="null" pageNumber="101" type="description">
<paragraph id="9C296F0FD6577D2C1530A7E57BD863E4" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">
Bis 1,5 m hohe Farne. Rhizom dick, meist senkrecht, mit Spreuschuppen bedeckt. 
<emphasis id="CD2EB74E74CB44BDFD8F4D09A17FF0AB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">
Sporentragende 
<normalizedToken id="5A1D90D1337E0DF923B01ECB793DD934" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
von den nicht sporentragenden auffallend verschieden
</emphasis>
. Nicht sporentragende 
<normalizedToken id="7C70A1007C6C1C0583D7BA66D6ED1665" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
1-2fach gefiedert. 
<emphasis id="AFA9A7B54B4010C8EB099E2A862538C1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">
Sporentragende 
<normalizedToken id="1900622A65674928FB710E1E34A65B64" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
mit bis zum Mittelnerv der Fiedern 1. Ordnung 
<normalizedToken id="35B96EC35988656C228C7BFFCE7F2748" originalValue="zurückgerolltem" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">zurueckgerolltem</normalizedToken>
, die Sori 
<normalizedToken id="AA1D3659CB5F3832CF8BDF71E6921675" originalValue="einschlieβendem" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">einschlieβendem</normalizedToken>
Rand
</emphasis>
. Schleier 
<normalizedToken id="9E2911F3764072AEBFD6815FBF46C6F1" originalValue="unterständig" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">unterstaendig</normalizedToken>
, nach dem Blattrand hin frei, den Sorus 
<normalizedToken id="D0711DFD9DA3C92266945BCE688D956B" originalValue="überdeckend" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">ueberdeckend</normalizedToken>
, aber bald einschrumpfend.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6AD66E6D5891F6C64BA7559A3188E818" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">
Die Gattung 
<normalizedToken id="AFFCA17841D1FC89BD8B4FEF5D788A29" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">umfasst</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="CBA720AB9C28326158ED3178A4C038D6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">
3 Arten: M. 
<taxonomicName id="6B73BA99E70D472AB806D9848C200AEE" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Blechnaceae" genus="Struthiopteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Struthiopteris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4882A17D35A0172212FE2BA80583AC51" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7615456C56D055A6B9E732981EF27EE5" authority="Trev. in Suedostasien" authorityName="Trev. in Suedostasien" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Onocleaceae" genus="Matteuccia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="1C3BF2FA02F262AE1811AF49BD8892CC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">M. orientalis</emphasis>
Trev. in 
<normalizedToken id="40F2997FD04349275FCE4787838D0FFC" originalValue="Südostasien" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">Suedostasien</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="65779E4BA502CF3914E0ED9909FA1B81" authority="Raymond" authorityName="Raymond" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Onocleaceae" genus="Matteuccia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pensylvanica">
<emphasis id="08A32C7FBB37B60C6B3108A3871F7AFB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="101">M. pensylvanica</emphasis>
Raymond
</taxonomicName>
im atlantischen Nordamerika.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
